metadata.name: Broken Symmetries #2/3 #77
metadata.description:
"It was the best of times, it was the worst of times, it was the age of wisdom, it was the age of foolishness, it was the epoch of belief, it was the epoch of incredulity, it was the season of Light, it was the season of Darkness, it was the spring of hope, it was the winter of despair, we had everything before us, we had nothing before us..."
Charles Dickens

This piece is the secon in a planed series of three intended as studies on composition.

It is built entirely on thi.ng/umbrella libraries and template:

https://github.com/thi-ng/fxhash-tpl

Keyboard shortcuts

- 1 : render @ original resolution
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution
- s : download canvas as SVG @ current resolution; This can be used with a plotter.

metadata.name: Wildwood Forest #537
metadata.description:
The Trees are the embodiment of a sanctorium. Anyone who knows how to speak to them and listen to them can embrace the truth. they preach the ancient law of life. Under these trees bushes that generate the flow of life in the darkened celestial sphere , with the greatest sun of spring's clear weather and again in fall when every leaf is a flower. And what magnificent bouquets the autumn leaves make.

Enjoy :)

---
Created using vanilla javascript

metadata.name: Perspective #14
metadata.description:
A few primitives and a lot of points.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Keys
s: Take a screenshot
space: Pause/Play the animation.
r: Play a new animation
↑: Increase point alpha
↓: Decrease point alpha
→: Increase point density
←: Decrease point density

URL Params
w: Width of the canvas - (ex, w=1024) - [0-2048]
h: Height of the canvas - (ex, h=1024) - [0-2048]
a: To set the alpha for the points - [0.0-1.0]
p: To set the total number of points to draw (in millions) [1-8]
s: Make the visual static - (ex, s=1)

metadata.name: Indistinct Places #17
metadata.description:
There's a certain state you fall into when you're half asleep that feels very warm and nostalgic. Most of the time, you imagine places or situations that are a mixture of the familiar and the unfamiliar, a strange brew of your past and the future you desire.
"Indistinct Places" is a tribute to this fuzzy state.

/////

Takes a long time to render.
In case you get bored: click on the canvas to start the algorithmic audio.

key "1" - "6": increases the render resolution by 2x with each step
-> These will automatically export a png after the simulation is done.
(Alternatively, you can contact me on Twitter and i can render a high res file in the size you need).

key "s": saves a png with the current resolution

Tone.js is used for the audio.

metadata.name: A Less Traveled Path #70
metadata.description:
"I shall be telling this with a sigh
Somewhere ages and ages hence:
Two roads diverged in a wood, and I—
I took the one less traveled by,
And that has made all the difference."

- Robert Frost, The Road Not Taken



=========

Controls:
[1] set resolution to 1024x1024 (default)
[2] set resolution to 2048x2048 
[3] set resolution to 4096x4096
[0] set resolution to window size (might help on lower end computers)

[c] capture a screenshot at rendered resolution


Made with cables.gl, a node-based webgl environment
XALTED 2022

metadata.name: Parametric Decoy #123
metadata.description:
The project started with the discovery of an unusual shape. Draw two parallel sine arcs and connect their opposite points. That's how you get one slice of Parametric Decoy. The shape may appear in its different phases. Sometimes elegant, sometimes awkward. Sometimes broken, sometimes symmetrical. Only connectivity stays the same.

Features:
- size: small, medium, large
- color: *several options*
- background: transparent, halftone, cutout
- distorted: no, maybe*, twisted, displaced, yes**

* "maybe" means I'm not quite sure if distortion affects visible part of the shape
** "yes" means combination of "twisted" and "displaced"

Press S to save. To download in custom size (ex. 2000px width), add &size=2000 to url, reload and press S.

Made with p5js, inspired by pop-art collages and my own geometric sketches

metadata.name: Hope #494
metadata.description:
Ups, downs, and everything in between. This series is about prevailing hope in the journey of life.
Each brush stroke is meant to elicit perspective, connectivity, beauty, and hope.

Features:
F  -  Fullscreen
S  -  Save image
2/4/6/8/0  -  Change image resolution (press number key and then reload in live view, please wait a few seconds for higher resolutions to load)

Designed in p5js
Original artwork, 2022 by fauxjebus and Dave Siegel

“To live without hope is to cease to live.”
- Fyodor Dostoyevsky

metadata.name: Bleached #14
metadata.description:
Bleached is a work inspired by mid-20th century art. I have always been impressed by its beauty and charm of non-ideality. How art gave birth to order out of utter chaos.
Inspired, I transferred the spirit of its freedom and expression into my algorithm.
